title: Analyst (Global Data and Analytics)
description:
Job Summary

As a member of the Global Analytics & Insights Team, Analyst is an everyday partner of multiple departments, including Global Marketing, Category Management, Shared Services & Finance, Global Technology, and Business Unit Leadership.

The Analyst is responsible for completing analytical and operational inquiries by developing thoughtful, and thorough practical analyses and reports to inform decisions and support business needs. Results must be highly polished and suitable for internal and external presentation. The Analyst to the Manager of Analytics.

Responsibilities/Accountabilities


Analyze sales & marketing programs and transactional customer data to identify causal relationships between sales & marketing initiatives and both store and customer profitability; perform ROI analysis that assists in optimizing marketing spend.
Conduct operational analyses in the areas of marketing, merchandising, food & beverage, and other areas of the business as needed.
Analyze in-market strategic initiatives and business performance using test and control analytics, benchmarking, statistical concepts, and financial measures to guide decision making by brand and sales teams.
Work closely with senior marketing and merchandising executives, category managers and Business Unit Leadership to enhance business performance.
Constructively challenge the status quo to advance and evolve how Circle K thinks about, and executes Pricing and Promotions, given internal and external / environmental trends.
Generate ad-hoc reporting and analysis as required.
Other duties as assigned.


Knowledge, Skills And Other Qualifications Required


Intermediate skill level with enterprise reporting systems and relational database management systems preferred.
Knowledge of SQL programming fundamentals and statistical analysis tools preferred.
Proficient in all Microsoft Office applications.
Able to learn and utilize additional analytics tools (e.g., R, Python, Microsoft Power BI, etc.) as needed.
Experience with Business Intelligence software, general ledger and point of sale applications preferred.


Education/Training Required


Bachelor’s degree required, preferably with quantitative focus (Economics, Finance, Math, Stats, Analytics)


Circle K is an Equal Opportunity Employer.

The Company complies with the Americans with Disabilities Act (the ADA) and all state and local disability laws. Applicants with disabilities may be entitled to a reasonable accommodation under the terms of the ADA and certain state or local laws as long as it does not impose an undue hardship on the Company. title: SQL Data Analysts
description:
SQL Data Analyst
Employment Type: Contract-to-Hire (1-3 months CTH)
Workplace Type: Onsite
Location: Mission Hills, CA (91345)
Industry: Construction/Equipment Rentals
Compensation: $42-48 hourly

DUTIES & RESPONSIBILITIES:

* Analyze and manipulate SQL data sets; test and debug issues with SQL reports; create and maintain SQL queries.
* Assist in the development of monthly reports and visual dashboards of customer data, including billings, revenue, and transactions for C-Level executives and the finance team.
* Manage, update, and maintain SQL databases.
* Utilize statistical programming languages to create automation scripts for analyzing and reporting data
* Extract, manipulate, and report data from financial and operations software systems.

REQUIREMENTS SKILLS:

* Bachelor's or Associate's Degree in Data Analytics, Computer Science, Software Engineering, or related fields (Preferred)
* 3-5+ years of experience working in a Data Analyst role working in a fast-paced environment analyzing and reporting SQL data.
* Ability to read, interpret, and created moderate to complete SQL query scripts.
* Knowledge and expeirnece with SQL Server Reporting Services (SSRS)
* Experiences using PowerBI or similar data visualization tools.
* Familiarity Python scripting for data automation purposes
* Strong skills with Microsoft Excel and experience using Pivot Tables and Formulas
* Experience extracting, manipulation, and reporting data information from financial and operations systems.

BONUS SKILLS:

* Certifications with SQL, Oracle, and Data Analytics
* Experience and knowledge of Oracle databases and PL/SQL scripting.
* Knowledge of Asset & Inventory Management and Sales/Rental Contract Management Software; familiarity with Basis Software is a huge plus!
* Familiarity with Adobe products

title: Data Analyst
description:
We are excited in your interest to join DC Health (The District of Columbia Department of Health), a nationally accredited Public Health Department (https://phaboard.org/). DC Health is focused on providing the essential public health services (10 Essential Public Health Services) necessary to protect and promote the health of all people in all communities and remove systemic and structural barriers that have resulted in health inequities through the Core Competencies for Public Health Professionals (PH Core Competencies.)

Skills

Come see where your knowledge, skills and abilities are appreciated, developed, and rewarded as you play a vital role in DC Health achieving its Strategic Priorities:


Promote a culture of health and wellness
Address the social determinants of health
Strengthen public-private partnerships
Close the chasm between clinical medicine and public health and
Implement data driven and outcome-oriented approaches to program and policy development.


Bring your professional career to Washington, D.C., the most dynamic and diverse city in the country. With its proximity to major museums, world class parks, entertainment, and restaurants, increasing job opportunities and the seat of the federal government, the District of Columbia continues to be ranked in the top 10 of thriving city indicators where you can live, work and play. We look forward to reviewing your candidacy, be well and good luck!

Job Summary

This position is located in the District of Columbia Department of Health (DC Health), HIV/AIDS, Hepatitis, STD, and TB administration (HAHSTA). The functions of this position include analytical and programmatic work to the improvement of public health services through evidence-based practices. The incumbent will be responsible for assisting on the management, assessment, development, and implementation of public health programs. The desired candidate will also support local programs and agencies to achieve healthy communities, work with them to achieve health equity and eliminate health disparities with special focus on supporting populations with high risk health factors.

Major Duties And Responsibilities

The incumbent serves as Data Analyst (Data Manager) under the general supervision of the Planning and Evaluation Manager. The successful candidate will serve as an expert on the database management and analytics of Ryan White Services Program; provide professional technical assistance to healthcare providers to ensure data guidelines compliance as a means of improving overall clinical measures and patients outcomes.

The candidate will also interpret and analyze data and make decisions utilizing techniques and resources from external and internal partnerships. As Data Manager for the program, they will lead the planning and delivery of annual reporting, including the Ryan White Services Report and other reports to federal and local agencies. Additionally, the candidate will govern the data reporting processes through our data system (CAREWare) developing and updating data quality dashboards.

Qualifications And Education

Individuals must possess at least one (1) year of specialized experience must have been equivalent to at least the next lower grade (11) level in the normal line of progression for the occupation in the organization. Specialized experience is defined as experience that is typically in or related to the work of the position to be filled, and has equipped you with the particular knowledge, skills, and abilities to successfully perform the duties of the position, and that is typically in or related to the work of the position to be filled.

Its strongly preferred candidates hold a degree in Public Health, Data Analytics, Health Informatics or data/systems-relate subject.

Licenses and Certifications

None required.

Working Conditions / Environment

The incumbent must be able to carry out official duties in a variety of settings and conditions. Routine work will occur primarily in an office setting.

Other Significant Facts

Agency Wide Consideration: Qualified individuals that submit applications for this vacancy may be considered for other current open vacancies for which they qualify within DC Health.

Tour of Duty: Monday - Friday 8:15am - 4:45pm

Area of Consideration: Open to the Public

Promotion Potential: No Known Promotion Potential

Duration of Appointment: Career Service – Term Appointment: 13 Month time limited

Pay Plan, Series and Grade: CS-0301-12

Collective Bargaining Unit (Union): This position is covered in a collective bargaining unit, represented by Local AFGE 2978 .

Position Designation

This position has been designated as Security Sensitive. Pursuant to section 410 of Chapter 4 of the D.C. Personnel Regulations; in addition to the general suitability screening, individuals applying for or occupying security sensitive positions are subject to the following checks and tests:


(a) Criminal background check;
(b) Traffic record check (as applicable);
(c) Consumer credit check (as applicable);
(d) Reasonable suspicion drug and alcohol test; and
(e) Post-accident or incident drug and alcohol test.


EEO Statement: The District of Columbia Government is an Equal Opportunity Employer. All qualified candidates will receive consideration without regard to race, color, religion, national origin, sex, age, marital status, personal appearance, sexual orientation, family responsibilities, matriculation, physical handicap, or political affiliation.

title: Data Analyst (Business Intelligence)
description:
As a Business Intelligence Analyst, you will join a driven, collaborative team within an ambitious, entrepreneurial global organization. You will work collaboratively within the Data & Analytics team supporting internal reporting for Global Client Services. This role requires a proactive individual who takes ownership of all assigned work and thrives in a collaborative team environment.

We pride ourselves on being a positive work environment, and place value on a work/life balance. This means thoughtful, sustainable workloads, as well as professional development opportunities to help you reach your career goals.

We are currently hiring out of the following office location(s):


Cherry Hill, NJ
Downers Grove, IL


This role may be eligible for voluntary work-from-home consideration. In order to be considered for this position, you should live within a commutable distance to one of these office locations, even if you plan to request a work-from-home arrangement, as there may be times when in-person meetings, training sessions, social events, or similar activities are held onsite.

This key position reports to the Director, Source-to-Pay Data & Analytics within our Advisory team. We're a dedicated, down-to-earth group in a growing organization offering plenty of opportunity. We look forward to adding you into the mix!

As a Business Intelligence Analyst, you will:


Handle diverse data inputs and transform them into valuable insights, demonstrating strong data organization and cleansing skills, ensuring that data is presented in a format that is clear and accessible to team members.
Utilize tools and techniques to clean and standardize data, ensuring accuracy and consistency.
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to understand business requirements and identify key outcomes for reporting.
Present findings and recommendations to stakeholders (technical and non-technical) in clear and concise formats
Demonstrate exceptional communication skills, documenting and articulating findings and action items



Requirements

You'll need to have:


Bachelor's or Master's in Mathematics, Statistics, Analytics, Business Information Systems, or a related field.
Proven experience with business intelligence software such as Power BI, Tableau, Qlik.
Excellent communication skills, written and verbal (English).
Knowledge in Programming Languages (SQL, Python) for querying and manipulating data stored in databases
Intermediate to advanced Microsoft Excel skills.
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with a keen attention to detail and a commitment to delivering high quality reporting
A strong work ethic, self-motivation and progressive thinking, thriving on new challenges.
Ability to self-manage and prioritize workload across multiple projects.


(We want to make sure you're set up to succeed, and we view these as the critical skills you'll need to achieve great things at Corcentric!)

As we continue to grow our Advisory practice, we are looking for the right people to join us on our mission. If you are interested in being part of our team, we would like to communicate the following:


We are energized by challenges and the effort needed to solve them
We like working with people who are positive, adaptable and growth minded
We prioritize both the process and outcome of work, demonstrating a strong commitment to the success of our customers and colleagues. Exceptional quality work is an essential standard for us.
We operate within a voluntary work-from-home framework, yet we uphold the same level of accountability and responsibility as in a traditional office setting



About Us

Corcentric is a global provider of business spend management and revenue management software and services for mid-market and Fortune 1000 businesses. Corcentric delivers software, advisory services, and payments focused on reducing costs, optimizing working capital, and unlocking revenue.

We achieve success by exemplifying our core values in the way we work, communicate, and collaborate:


Do the Right Thing
Embrace + Drive Change
Be Empowered
Be Relentlessly Focused on the Customer



Benefits

At Corcentric, we know that the hard work of our employees is what drives the success of our organization. We care about who you are and what you value, both inside and outside of work.

Within our organization, you will have the opportunity to work with smart, collaborative team members and approachable leaders. Our down-to-earth, solutions-oriented culture means you'll have the opportunity to get hands-on with interesting work projects and be able to draw a short line from your contributions to business impacts. We prioritize professional development and encourage cross-functional promotional opportunities to enable you to reach your career goals. We have been in business for over 25 years and are thrilled to be actively growing and scaling our teams accordingly - it's an exciting environment and a great time to join.

We also recognize the importance of work-life balance and want to support your efforts to take care of your health and well-being and the health and well-being of those who depend upon you. In support of this, we are proud to offer a comprehensive benefits package to our full-time team members, including:


Generous annual paid time off program that increases with tenure
Nine paid holidays plus an annual personal holiday to recognize or celebrate an occasion that is important to you
An annual paid day off to volunteer for causes that are near and dear to you
Paid maternity, paternal/secondary caregiver, and adoptive parent leave
Company-paid life and disability insurance
401k program with a company match
Medical insurance plan options ranging from a traditional PPO to High Deductible Health Plan options that feature a company HSA contribution
Dental plan - including orthodontia coverage
Vision plan - including discount for LASIK surgery
All medical, dental, and vision insurance plans are available from the first of the month following your start date - no extended waiting period to be eligible!
A no-cost Employee Assistance Program - 24/7 access to confidential counseling services and a wide range of additional support and professional services


Our roles require routine use of standard office equipment, such as computers, keyboards, printers, phones, and filing cabinets. You may need to type, reach, and lift office materials of a reasonable weight. Travel may also be required based on job responsibilities and business needs.

Corcentric does not discriminate on the basis of race, sex, color, religion, age, national origin, marital status, disability, veteran status, genetic information, sexual orientation, gender identity or any other reason prohibited by law in provision of employment opportunities and benefits.

title: Data Analyst
company: Mark Cuban Cost Plus Drug Company, PBC
description:
As a Data Analyst, you will be a key contributor to our mission of making affordable medications accessible to everyone. You will use your analytical skills and expertise to uncover valuable insights from complex datasets. These insights will directly guide our strategies, help us measure the impact of our initiatives, and ultimately improve patient affordability. This role is ideal for someone with a strong analytical mindset, technical skills, and the ability to translate complex data into clear recommendations.




DUTIES & RESPONSIBILITIES:

Data Cleaning and Preparation:

Collect, clean, and organize data from diverse sources.
Ensure data accuracy and completeness through validation.
Learn and apply data cleaning techniques to prepare data for analysis.




Data Analysis and Insights:

Assist in conducting analyses to identify trends, patterns, and key insights.
Support the creation of reports, dashboards, and visualizations that effectively communicate findings.
Translate complex data findings into actionable recommendations for stakeholders.




Data Quality:

Help identify and resolve data quality issues and discrepancies.
Learn about data quality standards and best practices in the healthcare industry.




Cross-Functional Collaboration:

Partner with various business units to support their data needs, including ad-hoc analysis and report generation.
Adapt your approach to meet the specific requirements of different teams.




Continuous Learning and Growth:

Actively participate in User Acceptance Testing (UAT) and System Testing to ensure data accuracy and system functionality.
Embrace opportunities to learn new skills and tools as our data landscape evolves.




EDUCATION AND/OR TRAINING:

Bachelor's degree in Statistics, Mathematics, Economics, Computer Science, or a related field.




WORK EXPERIENCE:

2+ years of experience in data analysis (healthcare or pharmaceutical experience is a plus).
Equivalent combination of education and industry experience will be considered.
“Power user” of Microsoft Excel or Google Sheets
Demonstrated ability to conduct ad hoc analyses under tight deadlines
Familiarity with SQL and data manipulation tools (Python or R is preferred)




ADDITIONAL QUALIFICATIONS:

Ability to work independently with little to no supervision.
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills
Passion for using data to answer questions and drive decisions
Meticulous attention to detail and commitment to data accuracy
Excellent communication and presentation skills
Enthusiasm for our mission of affordable medication access

title: Data Analyst
description:
Location: In Office 4 days/week in LA office

Who We Are:

Thrive Causemetics is Bigger Than Beauty™: We are an independent, female-owned beauty brand that creates high-performance vegan cosmetics and supports a community of giving. All of Thrive Causemetics' products are free of parabens and sulfates, in addition to being 100 percent cruelty-free. Through its Bigger Than Beauty™ program, every product you purchase results in a donation to help a woman thrive. Thrive Causemetics is dedicated to fostering a collaborative and cross-functional workplace where everyone’s voice matters. We are committed to being pioneers in creating a culture of wellness. Together, we prioritize a strong work ethic while maintaining a positive, exciting environment where people are passionate about what they do .

Who We Are Looking For:

The Data Analyst role at Thrive Causemetics is a hybrid role combining the skill sets of a data analyst, business intelligence analyst. You will work cross functionally with multiple departments, with a focus on growth marketing efforts (CRM, Search, Digital Marketing). This includes helping out with dashboard creation, data pipelines, inventory forecasting and other ad hoc data requests as needed.

What You Will Be Doing:


Apply creative problem-solving skills across various business domains, including marketing & demand planning, to address unique challenges
Leverage customer data analysis to refine and enhance marketing strategies for both e-commerce and brand marketing
Develop dashboards that blend data visualizations and tabular information, delivering real-time insights accessible to all departments
Daily / weekly / monthly KPI reporting for Marketing, Operations and Ecom
QA: Conduct quality assurance to ensure the accuracy of final reports and dashboards
Generate insights from marketing ad performance to improve our paid ad efficiency
Evaluate and improve current business processes related to data management by identifying opportunities for automation and streamlining
Translate data into easy-to-digest insights for non-analytical stakeholders
Fulfill ad hoc data requests and perform data queries as required


What Will Make You Stand Out:


Bachelor’s degree (or higher) in Mathematics, Statistics, Economics, Computer Science or related field
1+ year of SQL experience
1+ year of experience with Python for data analytics (pandas, sklearn, matplotlib, seaborn, plot.ly )
1+ year of experience with data visualization platforms (Tableau, Looker)


Thrive Causemetics is an Equal Opportunity Employer. Applicants must be authorized to work for any employer in the U.S. without current or future sponsorship for an immigration-related work benefit. Thrive Causemetics does not hire H-1B, F-1 CPT, OPT, or STEM OPT candidates for this role.

The base pay range for this role is $70,000 -$90,000, with the following factors determining the base pay at offer: skills, qualifications, experience. This range provides the opportunity to progress as you grow and develop within a role. Additionally, this role is also eligible for an annual discretionary bonus based on company and individual performance. title: Data Analyst
description:

Highlights:

Position will work on the Data Analytics team of a global logistics company
This is a hybrid remote position with 2 WFH days/week of the candidates choosingBase salary from 50-55k + bonus ranging from 6%-24% of salary. Pay reviews every 6 months.
Excellent benefits package- company pays 85% of employees’ healthcare costs, 6% 401k match, and other great benefits




Description:

title: Data Analyst
description:
Recognized as a 2024 Top Workplace by the Tennessean, EnableComp is the leading source of revenue cycle management solutions for complex claims in the US. We proudly partner with well over 1000+ hospitals across the US to help them maximize their revenue from complex claims.

Our Mission

We partner with healthcare providers to maximize reimbursement from complex claims payers by having the best people, processes, products and performance.

Our Vision

We enable healthcare providers to do what they do best.

Position Summary

The Data Analyst responsibilities will include but not limited to quantitative analysis and predictive modeling of healthcare data to provide management with statistical findings and conclusions.  The ideal candidate should be able to develop, collect and analyze metrics and data to formulate fact-based decisions and proactively implement process improvements through analysis of claim and operational data.




Key Responsibilities
Ability to transform complex datasets into executive-level summaries, and communicate findings clearly and succinctly
Managing multiple projects and deadlines so you will need excellent time management and prioritization skills to meet multiple deadlines
Demonstrated problem solving and critical thinking skills; strong understanding of analytics results, as well as the ability to identify a problem and develop and execute new solutions to obtain results
Effectively communicate results to key stakeholders and policy makers; communication of results include clean and well-organized presentations to reflect analytic methods used and to illustrate key decision points with sufficient detail to support comprehension and replication of the analysis
Data responsibilities include identifying necessary data elements to build measures, querying data to limit large data sets, joining tables to build analytic views, other data prep, and documentation of process and results; working with external data management team to receive, load, and analyze new data
Ability to communicate with BA and IT to understand requirements, socialize ideas among peers and document work product
Solid hands-on experience and knowledge of database concepts
Ability to work independently given minimal direction
Exceptional attention to detail and work product validation, as well as the ability to step back and see the big picture
Other duties as required




Requirements and Qualifications
Bachelor’s Degree
2+ years’ experience with analytics, reporting, and relational databases
2 years’ experience working in a healthcare, SaaS or other similar environment.
Expertise in Microsoft Excel, PowerPoint, and SQL Server
Familiarity with healthcare terminology such as diagnosis code, CPT, claim ID, DRG, inpatient, outpatient, etc.
Experience with BI tool (Power BI/Tableau/Qlik)
Experience with statistical models and predictive analytics
Equivalent combination of education and experience will be considered.
Must have strong computer proficiency and understand how to use basic office applications, including MS Office (Word, Excel, and Outlook).
Regular and predictable attendance.
To perform this job successfully, an individual must be able to perform each essential duty satisfactorily.  Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable qualified individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.




Special Considerations and Prerequisites
Strong communication and presentation skills; ability to explain complex analytic results to an audience of varying levels of technical understanding required
Exceptional attention to detail and work product validation
Strong planning, organizational, and multi-tasking skills
Strong research, analytical, and problem-solving skills
Strong communication skills, written and verbal
Ownership of body of work







EnableComp is an Equal Opportunity Employer M/F/D/V. All applicants will be considered for this position based upon experience and knowledge, without regard to race, color, religion, national origin, sexual orientation, ancestry, marital, disabled or veteran status. We are committed to creating and maintaining a workforce environment that is free from any form of discrimination or harassment.

title: SQL Data Analyst
description:
Our client a leading asset management firm, located in New York City is looking to hire a SQL Data Analyst. As a Data Analyst, your primary focus will be to develop and execute a comprehensive data strategy, establish robust data governance practices, and ensure efficient reporting solutions within our organization. You will play a pivotal role in shaping the data landscape, enabling data-driven decision-making, and optimizing data assets to drive business success. You will also work closely with the business to understand their data requirements and deliver solutions to support their needs. This is a Full Time Position. Citizens and those authorized to work in the U.S. are encouraged to apply. We are unable to sponsor currently. Qualified candidates should send their resumes (Word Format) along with salary expectations to careers@velocitysgi.com .

MUST HAVE AZURE SSIS (AZURE SYNAPSE)

Responsibilities


Design and implement a forward-looking data strategy that aligns with the organization's business objectives, incorporating industry best practices and emerging data technologies.
Define and maintain a scalable, efficient, and flexible data architecture that accommodates diverse data sources and formats, while enabling seamless data integration and access. Work closely with business stakeholders to align architecture with their requirements.
Design and develop robust ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) processes to efficiently move, cleanse, and transform data from various sources into a central data repository, meeting business needs.
Implement and manage master data management solutions to ensure data consistency, accuracy, and reliability across the organization, in collaboration with various departments.
Collaborate with business stakeholders to define reporting requirements and deliver business intelligence and reporting solutions that provide actionable insights. Work closely with various departments to understand their reporting needs.
Establish data quality standards, conduct data profiling, and implement data quality improvement processes to maintain data integrity, with consideration for business-specific data quality requirements.
Create and maintain comprehensive documentation of data assets, data flows, and data definitions, making it accessible to relevant business teams.
Continuously assess emerging data technologies and tools to keep the organization up-to-date and competitive.
Design and implement databases to reflect new and existing business requirements.
Evaluate current data designs and databases to determine needed, upgrades and improvements.
Design and automate various internal and external reports using SSRS, InDesign and Power BI.
Communicate with many different company stakeholders to assess needs and goals.
Interpret functional and business requirements, design and implement solutions and architecture suited to our current business model and enhance them.


QUALIFICATIONS


Bachelor's or Master's degree in Computer Science, Data Science, Information Systems, or a related field.
2+ years working experience in IT at Financial Institutions.
3+ years full stack development of enterprise applications and database solutions.
Hands on experience with SQL Server, Azure, SSRS, Power BI.
Experience in data architecture, data strategy, data governance, and reporting.
In-depth knowledge of database management systems, data modeling, ETL processes, and reporting tools
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills for collaboration with cross-functional teams and stakeholders
Knowledge of industry best practices and data management trends
Skills and Abilities:
Knowledge of business domain is recommended.
Proficiency in Azure data services and technologies.
Strong understanding of data architecture, data modeling, and data governance principles.
Knowledge of ETL processes and tools, particularly within the Azure ecosystem.
Experience with master data management (MDM) and data quality management.
Expertise in data reporting and analytics tools, especially those integrated with Azure.
In-depth knowledge of data security and compliance, including Azure security practices.
Excellent documentation and communication skills.
Expertise in T-SQL and SQL Server Data Management Services (SSMS), SQL Server Integration Services (SSIS), SQL Server Reporting Services (SSRS)Solid knowledge of T-SQL (SQL Server) which includes stored procedures, UDF's and query optimization.
Solid knowledge of ETL, SSRS and Power BI.
Experience in T-SQL, SSRS, Power BI and SQL Server database management system.
Good understanding of Azure environment and DevOps.
InDesign Automation a plus.


Salary 100-120k

title: Data Analyst
description:
About Bikky




Restaurants are the heart of our communities - where we go to celebrate life’s memorable moments with those we love, and find comfort and familiarity in the world. But while the digital and data revolutions have transformed other parts of commerce and hospitality, restaurants haven’t had the same opportunity. The result has been an industry that’s - on average - had their profit margins shrink by 5x over the past 20 years.




Bikky was founded on the belief that restaurants deserve the same access to data as the largest, most sophisticated businesses in the world. We believe that data can fundamentally transform the economic model of the entire restaurant industry - producing better businesses, more jobs, and stronger communities.




Bikky is based in New York City and has raised over $15 million in funding to date, most recently with a Series A in Q4 2023. We’re proud to serve thousands of restaurant locations across the U.S., including major brands like Bojangles, MOD Pizza, Dave’s Hot Chicken, and Long John Silver’s. 




About the role




As a Data Analyst, you’ll act as the bridge between our customers and our product. You’ll support customers through their journey adopting Bikky - starting from onboarding their data all the way to leveraging it for sophisticated analyses. You’ll be a key stakeholder in making sure that our customers understand Bikky’s insights and that we become a core part of their critical decision making processes. Unlike data roles that focus on internal analyses, at Bikky you’ll work across the entire restaurant industry - helping brands use their data to solve their hardest business challenges. 




From a technical perspective, you’ll have the opportunity to contribute throughout our entire data stack. A typical day might include everything from updating a DBT model to support a new customer’s needs, to performing an analysis on customer retention. You'll collaborate closely with our product and engineering teams to refine and enhance our data tools based on real-world customer feedback. Long term, there’s an opportunity to grow into a product development, data engineering, or data science role depending on where you’d like to take your career. 




About you




Our data roles are unique; they’re product and customer facing, rather than internal facing. To meet that challenge, we’re looking for candidates with a multidisciplinary skillset. In our interview process we’ll look for analysis experience, business sense, and interpersonal skills.




The ideal candidate will have: 

1-3 years of experience working with data
Fluency in SQL, experience with DBT a bonus 
Experience in a business facing or customer facing analytical role 
Strong statistical skills
Excellent verbal and written communication




This is a great role for candidates early in their careers or transitioning into data from a business role. That said, we want to talk with exceptional candidates from any background. If you feel you’re a great fit for the role, please reach out even if you don’t meet all of the points above. 




Why us




At Bikky, you’ll work on challenging problems that matter to real businesses while tackling industry leading technical challenges. Our DBT + Snowflake implementation is in the top ~1% of industry-wide sophistication and we grapple with novel data engineering, analytical, and product problems every day. Alongside challenging work, you’ll have the support of a fully Senior and Staff level team. You’ll be the first non-senior level hire and we’re deeply committed to making sure you’ll be successful. You’ll have the opportunity to accelerate your career by working alongside some of the best in the industry. 




Perks and Benefits

$100,000 - $140,000 annual salary 
Generous equity compensation
Top tier (for stage) health insurance including medical, vision, and dental 
Ability to participate in a 401k
Bikky offers a hybrid working environment. For candidates in New York City, we have an office where teammates can opt to work 2-3 times per week.
Flexible vacation policy

Strong communication skills, written and verbal
Ownership of body of work

Job Description

title: Entry Level Data Analyst
description:

Washington, DC




As an Entry-Level Data Analyst, you will play a crucial role in supporting data-driven initiatives. You will work closely with various teams to collect, analyze, and interpret data, helping to inform business decisions and strategies. Collect, clean, and analyze data from multiple sources to support business objectives.
Generate reports and visualizations to communicate findings to stakeholders.

title: Data Analyst
description:
Location: In Office 4 days/week in LA office

Who We Are:

Thrive Causemetics is Bigger Than Beauty™: We are an independent, female-owned beauty brand that creates high-performance vegan cosmetics and supports a community of giving. All of Thrive Causemetics' products are free of parabens and sulfates, in addition to being 100 percent cruelty-free. Through its Bigger Than Beauty™ program, every product you purchase results in a donation to help a woman thrive. Thrive Causemetics is dedicated to fostering a collaborative and cross-functional workplace where everyone’s voice matters. We are committed to being pioneers in creating a culture of wellness. Together, we prioritize a strong work ethic while maintaining a positive, exciting environment where people are passionate about what they do .

Who We Are Looking For:

The Data Analyst role at Thrive Causemetics is a hybrid role combining the skill sets of a data analyst, business intelligence analyst. You will work cross functionally with multiple departments, with a focus on growth marketing efforts (CRM, Search, Digital Marketing). This includes helping out with dashboard creation, data pipelines, inventory forecasting and other ad hoc data requests as needed.

What You Will Be Doing:


Apply creative problem-solving skills across various business domains, including marketing & demand planning, to address unique challenges
Leverage customer data analysis to refine and enhance marketing strategies for both e-commerce and brand marketing
Develop dashboards that blend data visualizations and tabular information, delivering real-time insights accessible to all departments
Daily / weekly / monthly KPI reporting for Marketing, Operations and Ecom
QA: Conduct quality assurance to ensure the accuracy of final reports and dashboards
Generate insights from marketing ad performance to improve our paid ad efficiency
Evaluate and improve current business processes related to data management by identifying opportunities for automation and streamlining
Translate data into easy-to-digest insights for non-analytical stakeholders
Fulfill ad hoc data requests and perform data queries as required


What Will Make You Stand Out:


Bachelor’s degree (or higher) in Mathematics, Statistics, Economics, Computer Science or related field
1+ year of SQL experience
1+ year of experience with Python for data analytics (pandas, sklearn, matplotlib, seaborn, plot.ly )
1+ year of experience with data visualization platforms (Tableau, Looker)


Thrive Causemetics is an Equal Opportunity Employer. Applicants must be authorized to work for any employer in the U.S. without current or future sponsorship for an immigration-related work benefit. Thrive Causemetics does not hire H-1B, F-1 CPT, OPT, or STEM OPT candidates for this role.

The base pay range for this role is $70,000 -$90,000, with the following factors determining the base pay at offer: skills, qualifications, experience. This range provides the opportunity to progress as you grow and develop within a role. Additionally, this role is also eligible for an annual discretionary bonus based on company and individual performance. Thrive Causemetics provides a competitive benefits package, including but not limited to: comprehensive medical, dental and vision plans, a 401(k) plan with employer matching, various paid time off programs, employee discount/perks, life insurance, disability insurance, and employee assistance programs.

description:

Position will work on the Data Analytics team of a global logistics company
This is a hybrid remote position with 2 WFH days/week of the candidates choosingBase salary from 50-55k + bonus ranging from 6%-24% of salary. Pay reviews every 6 months.

As the Data Analytics Coordinator, you will Partner with key stakeholders to establish and implement data-driven metrics designed to improve internal business processes, support strategic planning, and ultimately improve profitability. title: Data Analyst
description:
Job Title: Data Analyst

Job Location: Savannah GA 31406

Onsite Requirements:

Running SQL queries to pull data from Snowflake
Build reporting from data using Qlik
Strong understanding of business metrics/KPIs

Job Description:

Essential Functions / Duties Performed Regularly:

Analyze and interpret data from various marketing campaigns to uncover trends, patterns, and insights related to performance and identify areas for improvement.
Monitor and evaluate call center metrics, such as call volumes, service levels, customer satisfaction, and resolution times.
Develop and maintain dashboards and reports that track key performance indicators (KPIs) and marketing effectiveness.
Collaborate with marketing teams to design and implement A/B testing frameworks and measure the impact of various campaigns.
Provide data-driven recommendations to optimize marketing spend and improve return on investment (ROI).
Work with customer service managers to improve call center operations and customer engagement strategies.
Utilize advanced analytics techniques to forecast trends and model potential outcomes of marketing and customer service initiatives.
Stay abreast of industry trends and advancements in analytics and performance marketing tools.

Minimum Qualifications:

Education: Bachelor's degree in Statistics, Mathematics, Economics, Computer Science, or related field or equivalent combination of education and experience.
Work Experience: Minimum of 5 years of experience in a data analysis role, preferably within a marketing or advertising context.

Knowledge, Skills and Abilities:

Analytical Skills: Ability to interpret complex data sets and provide actionable insights.
Statistical Knowledge: Proficiency in statistical tests, distributions, and regression analysis.
Data Visualization: Skill in creating clear visual representations of data using tools like Tableau or Power BI.
SQL: Strong command of SQL for querying databases.
Programming Languages: Proficiency in programming languages - SQL, Python, R, or other data analysis tools.
Machine Learning: Understanding of basic machine learning algorithms and their application in marketing data.
A/B Testing: Experience in designing and interpreting A/B tests to optimize campaign performance.
Data Mining: Ability to extract data from various sources and prepare it for analysis
Strong communication skills: Ability to translate complex data into actionable insights for non-technical stakeholders.

Physical Requirements:

Standing, walking, sitting, movement and use of mechanical controls, such as keyboard, are frequently required.
